{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 1918255, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "unholydriver", "body": "He is in the Siege or Orgrimmar raid just after you enter Orgrimmar. Some of the guards clearly were holding him captive but after Aysa yelled for him I missed what happened. Either they ran off with him or killed him. However, I don't think he was killed because they would have left his body.\n\nedit: Aysa carries Ji out back through the gates (Ji is alive).", "date": "2013-11-14T13:27:59-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-11-14T22:37:36-06:00", 1, "unholydriver"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 1902723, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "jeremyjw", "body": "i have been told that if you wait long enough [url=www.wowhead.com/npc=72455]Overseer Komak[/url] will kill Ji", "date": "2013-09-25T20:22:29-05:00", "rating": 11, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I can confirm Ji does, in fact, get executed, slow LFR group. There is an RP scene between Ji and Aysa afterwards.", "creationdate": "2013-10-13T11:54:46-05:00", "id": 700902, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1902723, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ramajuko", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Also, if Ji dies, Aysa flips out and swears to kill Komak. Given what happened the last time a panda was angry enough to go on a killing spree (see Suna Silentstrike), killing their loved ones is a VERY BAD idea.", "creationdate": "2014-05-30T18:31:12-05:00", "id": 748776, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1902723, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Elyseon", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 1912303, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "TevishSzat", "body": "It's unfortunate, but this is probably the last we see of Ji Firepaw.  Theoretically, you can save him from execution for an achievement (Rescue Raiders)... but you can also get Gamon to battle Nazgrim for an achievement -- Where they present diverging plotlines, I'd personally guess \"no achievement\" to be the canon route.\r\n\r\nSo, what does his death mean for the Horde?  Will Chen Stormstout represent Pandaren among the horde, or will they simply be forgotten?  Likely the latter, and not without reason -- there weren't that many non-player pandaren in the Horde to begin with, and we've done an awfully good job of offending and alienating them at every turn.  It's mostly Garrosh's fault, but wounds like those we've inflicted (as embodied in the Vale and on Ji here) don't heal as easily as punching out one Orc.\r\n\r\nIn short, R.I.P. Horde/Pandaren relations.", "date": "2013-10-26T18:26:57-05:00", "rating": -11, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I'm pretty sure the existence of the achieves means both Gamon and Ji live on.", "creationdate": "2013-10-30T12:18:48-05:00", "id": 704674, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1912303, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "diddlywhat", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yeah, I'd assume the achievements are canon. I still don't expect to see Ji and Aysa again, though, since they went back to the turtle.", "creationdate": "2013-10-30T14:06:19-05:00", "id": 704691, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1912303, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Reignac", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Aysa does make mention of Ji again in the book about Garrosh's trial, suggesting he's around, but he's not shown directly. I'm sure glad he made it out, and found it rather amusing that she was the one to carry him out. His impulsiveness always had a habit of getting him in trouble and angering her, but in the end it looks like things turned out all right.", "creationdate": "2014-05-30T18:28:53-05:00", "id": 748775, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1912303, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Elyseon", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
